  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Felony charges\n- Significant prison time (often 5-20 years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset seizure\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Professional consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Damage to personal and professional reputation\n\n4. Civil penalties\n- Additional financial sanctions\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\nSpecific consequences depend on the jurisdiction, amount of money involved, and specific circumstances of the case.",
